14/09/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUFOR Commander Major General Gian Marco Chiarini and the NATO HQ Commander in BiH, Brigadier General Louis W. Weber, praised on Wednesday (13 September) progress made in transferring more responsibilities from international peacekeeping troops to BiH authorities. The two released a joint statement after the 46th meeting of the Joint Military Commission, announcing the handover of more responsibilities in the field of arms production and storage control from the EUFOR and NATO to the BiH authorities. (RTRS, Srna - 13/09/06)
